\subsubsection{A spy or thief acquires an ability unique to his skill.}

A spy may use his photographic memory ability to recall spoken
phrases.  Even if a spy does not know the language us- ed, he can
reproduce the phrases phonetically.  Additionally, when a spy
concentrates for (60 - 5 \x Rank) seconds, he can extend his
range of vision and hearing to (100+ 15 \x Rank])07o of %%-hat
it normally is.

A thief can, as long as he may find a purchase sufficient to bear his
weight, climb any structure.  His success chance when climbing on a
structure not made for that purpose is (4 \x MD + 10 \x
Rank) - (Structure Height in Feet / 10)\%.  Round the structure height
down.  If the GM's roll is greater than the success percentage, the
thief has fallen in climbing the structure.  To determine the height
at which the thief falls, roll D100.  Round the number off to the
nearest 10\% (a roll of 5 is rounded down), and multiply the height
the thief sought to attain by that percentage.  A thief suffers
([Structure Height in Feet/ 10] Squared) Endurance Points when he
falls.
